Burst Mode















Burst Mode Rules

The following rules apply to burst mode.

• The status of each command is carried over before and after activating burst mode.
(Abilities after change, etc.)
*Abilities transformed from BRV Attack and HP Attack for a certain number of uses are carried over along with their use counts.

• Once any character in a party enters burst mode, the remaining party members cannot activate burst commands.

• In co-op, each player can activate burst mode once.

• Burst mode commands are reflected in the character's equipped weapon and passive abilities.

• The duration remaining for buffs, debuffs, and special effects does not decrease during burst mode, and will decrease by 1 following the finishing burst.
*The duration remaining for buffs that cannot be extended will decrease.
*It is possible to grant new buffs, debuffs, and special effects.

BT Abilities


• Call abilities and BT abilities cannot be used during burst mode.

• During burst mode, abilities with limited uses will have 1 use and abilities with recast gauges will be full.
*Once burst mode ends, remaining uses and gauges will be returned to their pre-burst mode amounts.

• During burst mode, the recast gauge for EX abilities will not fill.

• Actions during burst mode will not add to the turn count. After the finishing burst, the turn count will increase by 1.

• If the enemy is knocked back during burst mode, all allies will join in the chain attack.

• If all enemies are defeated during burst mode, you will proceed to the next battle or be moved to the results screen after the finishing burst.

• You cannot summon or swap out friends during burst mode.

• You cannot activate burst mode while summoning.

• You will not enter burst mode while using burst commands when receiving support. You will go directly into the finishing burst.

• Using burst commands from support will not count toward your one use as a party.

• Burst commands may be used again when continuing.

• While burst effects from realized BT weapons are active, the name of the burst command will be changed to "Burst+."
